modules.description: This module creates a session manager that handles session lifecycle operations using a custom backend and cookie-based session identifiers. It provides functions to load sessions from a cookie header, generate new sessions, update session values or expiration, and clear sessions, with support for generating appropriate HTTP response headers. It works with backend-specific keys, values, and time periods, and is used to manage user sessions in web applications by persisting session state server-side and tracking sessions via cookies.

This module defines operations for creating, validating, and managing session cookies, including functions to generate secure tokens, set expiration times, and serialize cookie data. It works with string-based identifiers, timestamp values, and cookie-specific metadata such as domain and path. Concrete use cases include authenticating user sessions in web applications and securely maintaining state across HTTP requests.
